<TITLE> Secretaries shuffled </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 30 (bdnews24.com)The establishment ministry on Tuesday changed a number of secretaries and additional secretaries in an administrative shuffle. Dr Kamal Abdul Naser Chowdhury, additional secretary at the information ministry, has been made acting secretary at the ministry. Samar Chandra Paul, acting secretary, information, will head rural development and cooperatives. Abdul Awal Majumder, additional secretary, agriculture ministry, has been sent to the science and ICT ministry. Mahbub Ahmed, additional establishment secretary, goes to the youth and sports ministry as acting secretary. Ehsanul Fattah, youth and sports secretary, has been sent to land ministry. Delwar Hossain, land secretary, has been appointed as the Rector of Public Administration Training Centre. ABM Abdul Huq, textile and jute secretary, has been appointed as the chairman of Land Appeals Board. Ashraful Moqbul, chairman of the Board, takes his place. bdnew
